description.plain:
Shermar Paul (born May 29, 1997), better known by his stage name Night Lovell, is a rapper and producer from Ottawa, Canada. His old producer alias is KLNV standing for Killanov. He initially gained fame after his song “Dark Light” went viral online.

His name Night Lovell came from the middle name of his father, Lovell, and Night comes from the fact that he only records at night and finds he is the most productive in the darkness and silence that the night time brings. In an interview with The FADER he said:

I just feel like it’s a more vulnerable time of the day. That’s when people’s darkest secrets come out. It’s just a really personal time, so I feel like when I make music at that time it kind of sounds different.

His rapping style is known for his deep voice and usage of both cloud rap and electronic beats.

On December 21, 2014 he released his debut album named Concept Vague. Later on his second album Red Teenage Melody was released on June 13, 2016. In summer 2018 he revealed the name of his third album GOODNIGHT LOVELL, which was released on February 22nd, 2019.

description.plain:
Track 15 on Concept Vague by Night Lovell, produced by Lovell himself. Though this was the song that gave him massive exposure, Lovell revealed in an interview that he hates the song, but continues to perform it as his fans love the song very much, and as it’s his most popular song to date.

Lovell said he wrote the lyrics in his high school English class the day he recorded it, and the lyrics literally mean nothing. He said he had no direction in writing and “just threw words together.” This is what inspired the name of Lovell’s debut album Concept Vague, as he says most of the songs on the album mean nothing at all.

After uploading it to SoundCloud, it gained thousands of streams practically overnight, eventually gaining millions. Lovell said he was unaware of this until one of his friends texted him and informed him of the song’s popularity.

“Dark Light” currently has over fifteen million streams on SoundCloud and 20 million on YouTube. The sample loop heard throughout the video is NOT sampled from Jaden Smith’s “Chase The Sun”, but a seed mantra that is chanted throughout meditation.

Fun Fact: The song was the second song Lovell ever recorded.

“JOAN OF ARC” is Night Lovell’s single with fellow rappers $UICIDEBOY$. This song was teased on Twitter a few days before its official release, however, finally released by Lovell in the early morning of 30th May 2018, coinciding with Night Lovell’s birthday.

https://twitter.com/nightlovell/status/998722030253035520

With $UICIDEBOY$ hailing from New Orleans, the single cover artwork for “JOAN OF ARC,” as well as the name of the song, pay homage to the Heroine of France, Joan of Arc (French: Jeanne d'Arc), nicknamed “The Maid of Orléans,” who died on the release day of the song – 30th May, 2018 – 587 years ago.
